\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 HOLDINGS: [1]-In a former employee's religious discrimination case under }{\f5\fs28\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 Title VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 , the district court did not err in considering a deposition transcript submitted by the employer. The employer filed the certification required by }{\f5\fs28\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 Fed. R. Civ. P. 30(f)(1)}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  when the employee raised the issue; [2]-The employee's claim failed because allowing the employee to skip mandatory Saturday overtime shifts after he explained his religious concern constituted a reasonable accommodation. The employer was not required to offer the employee his preferred accommodation of making up the overtime hours on Sunday.}
