\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs28\b1\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 HN6}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  }{\f3\fs28\b1\i0\cf1 \~Burdens of Proof, Burden Shifting}
\par\plain {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 A plaintiff bears the initial burden to show a prima facie case of religious discrimination for failure to accommodate. The plaintiff must show that he has a bona fide religious belief that conflicts with an employment requirement, informed the employer of this belief, and was fired for failure to comply with the conflicting employment requirement. If the plaintiff satisfies his burden, the burden will shift to the employer, which will need to conclusively rebut an element of the plaintiff's prima facie case, show the offering of a reasonable accommodation, or show an inability to reasonably accommodate the plaintiff's religious beliefs without undue hardship.}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb120\ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \li360\ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 Labor & Employment Law\~>\~...\~>\~Religious Discrimination\~>\~Defenses\~>\~Reasonable Accommodation & Undue Hardship}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs28\b1\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 HN7}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  }{\f3\fs28\b1\i0\cf1 \~Defenses, Reasonable Accommodation & Undue Hardship}
\par\plain {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 Accommodate means allowing a plaintiff to engage in his religious practice despite the employer's normal rules to the contrary. But a reasonable accommodation does not necessarily spare an employee from any resulting cost. Thus, the accommodation may be reasonable even though it is not the one that the employee prefers.}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb120\ql\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24
\par\pard\plain \li360\ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 Labor & Employment Law\~>\~...\~>\~Religious Discrimination\~>\~Defenses\~>\~Reasonable Accommodation & Undue Hardship}
\par\pard\plain \ri-1600\sb240\sl260\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs28\b1\i1\ul\ulc0\cf4\cb2\highlight2 HN8}{\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1  }{\f3\fs28\b1\i0\cf1 \~Defenses, Reasonable Accommodation & Undue Hardship}
\par\plain {\f1\fs28\b0\i0\cf1 Unpaid leave eliminates a conflict between employment requirements and religious practices by allowing the individual to observe fully religious holy days and requires him only to give up compensation for a day that he did not in fact work.}
